	Renesas M3Le Geist BSP ROM Writer
	for Linux

2026/04/14	Kuninori Morimoto <kuninori.morimoto.gx@renesas.com>
=============================================
-------------------------------
* Preparation
-------------------------------

**  Necessary Tools

	You can install necessary tools by tool_install.xxx.
	If you are using Ubuntu, you can run.

		> ${renesas-bsp-rom-writer}/script/tool_install.ubuntu

**  ROM

	You need prepare Yocto ROM.
	see
		[How to get ROM ?]
		${renesas-bsp-rom-writer}/board/e3_ebisu/README

-------------------------------
* RL78
-------------------------------

	You can control several things via RL78 serial.
	It works with "921600 bps" baud-rate.

	- Power ON			"POWER#ON"
	- Power OFF			"POWER#OFF"
	- SCIF Download mode		"MD#7C0400"
	- HyperFlash boot  (80MHz)	"MD#640400"
	- HyperFlash boot (160MHz)	"MD#240400"
	- QSPI boot			"MD#140400"
